RACE.RACE_TEXT: MEADOWLANDS RACE 1 5F Turf CR: 74. Claiming Purse 17000. (PLUS UP TO 40% NJB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 16 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500, For Each $500 To $6,500 1 lb.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SEDONA ROCKS broke a step slow, raced off the pace, advanced at the quarter pole, angled out at the top of the lane, commenced a rally in midstretch, closed strongly outside and surged late to get up at the wire. VINDICATO raced off the pace inside, advanced inside on the turn, angled off the rail, bid at the furlong marker, took over, drew clear, dug in gamely and was caught at the finish. SHOW EM THE LIGHTS vied four wide for the early lead, chased four wide on the turn, rallied mildly in the final furlong and got up for third. TI SENTO (IRE) was bumped at the start, dueled inside for the lead, shook free on the turn, led into the stretch, dug in on the rail and then weakened. UNCLE REMI tracked close up on the inside, raced two wide at the quarter pole and lacked a winning bid. LITTLE J P was bumped at the start, dueled three wide for the lead, chased three wide on the turn and weakened in the lane. ROCKIN THE BANK was bumped at the start, dueled two wide for the lead, chased two wide on the turn and tired. CONSTITUTIONAL BID was bumped and steadied at the start, outrun early and closed belatedly inside.

FOREVER HOPEFUL raced off the pace between rivals and did not factor. HARLEE was reluctant to load, raced two wide off the pace, went three wide on the backside and gave way.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEVILS ONLY FRIEND quickly established a clear lead, showed the way racing on the inside, responded when roused, dug in gamely on the rail when challenged in midstretch and determinedly held off the runner up. LOST A LEGEND stalked the pacesetter early on, chased on the turn, rallied two wide nearing the furlong marker, moved up alongside of DEVILS ONLY FRIEND to challenged and dueled to the wire. BOOM BOOM KABOOM raced two wide off the pace, came three wide into the lane and lacked a rally. PRACTICAL WAY raced off the pace inside, steadied nearing the turn, then failed to threaten. RACE.FOOTNOTES: BINGO STAR chased two wide early, moved up inside on the turn, rallied on the rail in the stretch run, closed well, gained command nearing the sixteenth marker and drew clear under urging. GET LOADED raced off the pace, off the rail, advanced on the turn, moved up between rivals into the stretch, angled out, rallied outside and finished well late. WITHOUT A NET showed good early speed outside, cleared the field, showed the way into the stretch, dueled between rivals passing the furlong marker and was outkicked. NEVER PERSONAL was bumped at the start, raced off the pace, advanced on the turn, lugged out at the quarter pole, then rallied mildly outside in the lane. YELOMA chased inside, steadied at the seven sixteenths pole, moved up inside on the turn, rallied three wide into the stretch, bid and weakened. TWYLA trailed the field on the inside and closed belatedly on the rail. HARD TO CATCH chased four wide early, then three wide on the turn and weakened. ZULLY BELLA chased the pace, raced between rivals on the turn and tired. MY REAL DREAM was bumped at the start, chased three wide, steadied at the seven sixteenths marker, then failed to threaten. ROXEN refused at the break, then walked off. After a Steward's Inquiry into the start, the race was declared official.
